summary:
I am a visual artist with a BFA in Visual Arts Education and a BA in Public Relations. 

My main focus has been in teaching and developing my art research, centered on the interaction between the Fine Arts and Contemporary practices. I also have vast experience in different areas which includes planning and coordination of cultural programmes, art portfolio review,  art direction, design,  performing arts and publicity.

I have also worked as Event Meeting Executive, mostly in planning and coordination, for national and international companies and art galleries. I simultaneously worked towards earning my BFA and did a number of specialization courses.

Between 2016 - 2019 I worked intensively on my artistic research,  participating in art labs and seminars both in Buenos Aires, Argentina and Milano, Italy, where I stayed for one year. 

In 2020 I moved to The Netherlands, where I continue developing my teaching and artistic career.
